ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The age distribution of cases is not stated in this news report but the
inclusion of school and daycare workers implies that young children are
among the cases. Small outbreaks of pertussis are not uncommon and may
occur in unvaccinated or incompletely vaccinated children (including those
less than 1 year old who have not yet completed immunization) and older
children and adults in whom vaccine immunity has waned. Pertussis can be
troubling and debilitating (presenting as prolonged cough) but is rarely
fatal in this older group. Some apparent outbreaks occur when surveillance
and detection are enhanced. - Mod.LM]
